cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with a problem in computer vision and affect computing, specifically cross-database non-frontal expression recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel transductive deep transfer learning architecture, which involves training a neural network to learn optimal features from the source and target databases. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves experiments on facial expression databases, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
